From c49d72038e52a2c683b0a464092e9e7f5835ad49 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gahingwoo <huhuvmb88@outlook.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 16:10:56 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 07/17] arm64: dts: rockchip: run all RKNN clocks during
 NPU0/NPU1 power transitions

The BSP driver enables every NPU clock (CLK_RKNN_DSU0, ACLK_RKNN0/1,
HCLK_RKNN_ROOT, ACLK/HCLK_RKNN_CBUF) before powering on the NPU0/NPU1
domains and keeps them running through the whole transition.  Our
NPU0/NPU1 domain nodes only listed HCLK_RKNN_ROOT and the per-core
ACLK, so the domains powered on with the DSU core clock and the CBUF
clocks gated.  Without the functional clock running, the power-on
sequencing never propagates through the core block: the domain reports
on, the idle handshake completes, but every register in the block
(including the IOMMU banks at core+0x2000) reads back dead, which is
exactly the

  rk_iommu: Error during raw reset. MMU_DTE_ADDR is not functioning

failure on the first runtime resume.  It also explains why pulsing the
BIU reset at power-on did not help -- with the clocks gated the
synchronous reset cannot propagate either.

Add CLK_RKNN_DSU0 and the CBUF clocks to both domain nodes so the
pmdomain core keeps them running across the transition, matching the
clock state the BSP guarantees.

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
index 6bd772b84..bb4fe4b18 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3576.dtsi
@@ -1070,7 +1070,10 @@ power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPUTOP {
 						power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPU0 {
 							reg = <RK3576_PD_NPU0>;
 							clocks = <&cru HCLK_RKNN_ROOT>,
-								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN0>;
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN0>,
+								 <&cru CLK_RKNN_DSU0>,
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN_CBUF>,
+								 <&cru HCLK_RKNN_CBUF>;
 							resets = <&cru SRST_A_RKNN0_BIU>;
 							pm_qos = <&qos_npu_m0>;
 							#power-domain-cells = <0>;
@@ -1078,7 +1081,10 @@ power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPU0 {
 						power-domain@RK3576_PD_NPU1 {
 							reg = <RK3576_PD_NPU1>;
 							clocks = <&cru HCLK_RKNN_ROOT>,
-								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN1>;
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN1>,
+								 <&cru CLK_RKNN_DSU0>,
+								 <&cru ACLK_RKNN_CBUF>,
+								 <&cru HCLK_RKNN_CBUF>;
 							resets = <&cru SRST_A_RKNN1_BIU>;
 							pm_qos = <&qos_npu_m1>;
 							#power-domain-cells = <0>;
